Add a screenshot interaction that clicks the remove button on a custom token to reveal the confirmation modal.

**Why impactful**: The token removal modal (Tokens/index.tsx lines 91-99) is a destructive action confirmation. Testing catches the modal rendering over the token list and validates the confirmation flow UI. The mock state already has 2 custom tokens (USDC, DAI), so the remove button should be visible.

**Interaction to add** to the interactions object:
```js
tokens: [
  ...(existingTokensInteractions || []),
  {
    name: 'remove-token-modal',
    js: \`(() => {
      // Find a remove/delete/trash button next to a token entry
      const btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('main button'));
      // Look for buttons with trash icon, 'Remove', 'Delete', or '×' text
      const removeBtn = btns.find(b => 
        b.textContent.includes('Remove') || 
