Add a screenshot interaction that fills in the Send form with a recipient address, selects a token, enters an amount, and triggers a validation error for insufficient balance.

**Why impactful**: The Send view form with filled fields tests the form layout under real conditions — selected network badge, token dropdown populated, amount field, and the error message styling. Testing the error state catches red error text rendering and disabled submit button styling.

**Interaction to add** to the interactions object:
```js
send: [
  {
    name: 'send-filled-form',
    js: \`(() => {
      const nativeSetter = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(window.HTMLInputElement.prototype, 'value').set;
      // Find recipient input and fill it
      const inputs = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('input'));
      const recipientInput = inputs.find(i => i.placeholder?.includes('0x') || i.name === 'recipient');
      if (recipientInput) {
        nativeSetter.call(recipientInput, '0xdeadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeef');
        recipientInput.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
        recipientInput.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
      }
      // Find amount input and set a large value to trigger insufficient balance
      const amountInput = inputs.find(i => i.placeholder?.includes('0.0') || i.type === 'number' || i.name === 'amount');
      if (amountInput) {
        nativeSetter.call(amountInput, '999999');
        amountInput.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
        amountInput.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
      }
      return 'filled recipient and amount, inputs found: ' + inputs.length;
    })()\`
  }
]
```

**Files to modify**: scripts/_screenshot_main.cjs (add send interaction)
**Source**: app/views/Send/index.tsx lines 275-295 for amount input and error/submit button
**Validate**: Run 'npm run test:screenshots' and verify the screenshot shows the Send form with a filled recipient address, amount field, and ideally an error message about insufficient balance.

